## API Endpoints and Command Line Invocations

**Analytics API Endpoints:**
- `POST /2/httpapi` - Event ingestion endpoint for real-time data collection
- `GET /2/events/segmentation` - Event segmentation query API
- `GET /2/users/{user_id}` - User profile and property retrieval
- `POST /identify` - User property updates and identification
- `GET /2/funnels` - Funnel analysis data retrieval

**Experiment API Endpoints:**
- `GET /v1/vardata` - Feature flag and variant configuration retrieval
- `POST /v1/assignment` - Experiment assignment and exposure tracking
- `GET /v1/experiments/{id}/results` - Experiment results and statistical analysis
- `POST /v1/flags` - Feature flag management and configuration

**Guides and Surveys API:**
- `GET /v1/guides` - In-product guide configuration retrieval
- `POST /v1/surveys/responses` - Survey response submission
- `GET /v1/targeting` - User targeting and segmentation rules

**Ampli CLI Commands:**
- `ampli pull` - Download tracking plan and generate type-safe code
- `ampli status` - Verify implementation against tracking plan
- `ampli login` - Authenticate with Amplitude workspace
- `ampli init` - Initialize new Ampli project configuration

**SDK Configuration Examples:**
- Route patterns like `/analytics/{slug}`, `/sdks/analytics/{platform}/{slug}`, `/feature-experiment/{slug}`
- Navigation injection with identifiers like `analytics`, `experiment_sdks`, `data`
- Multi-site support with language localization (`sites: [en, jp]`)
- Content mounting with UUID-based identifiers for modular documentation

The platform emphasizes developer experience through comprehensive documentation, migration guides, troubleshooting resources, and academy content for user education and onboarding.